          %h2 Foreman Switches Your Apps Quickly and It's Amazing
          %p Look at all these open apps:
          %p
            %img{:src => "/assets/images/foreman/somanyapps.png"}
          %p What a pain in the ass! But look what happens after I click an app group in Foreman:
          %p
            %img{:src => "/assets/images/foreman/phew.png"}
          %p My heavens! What a relief!
          %p If you do distinct tasks that require different sets of apps to be open, then Foreman will help you.
          %p You define app groups by dragging apps from the Finder into the space that says "Drag Apps Here To Create New Group".
          %p Then when you click on an app group, Foreman closes all open applications which aren't in that group. It also opens all the apps in that group that aren't already open.
          %p <strong>Holy smokes!!!!!</strong>

